style=3D'line-height:115%'>In a week in which he worked 45 hours the employ=
ee’s
regular rate of pay would be $220.00 divided by 45 hours, or $4.88. In addi=
tion
to the $220.00 already paid to him under his guaranty, he would be entitled=
 to
receive half-time for the five OT hours, or $12.20.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(2)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp; </span></span><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>In a week in which the employee worked 50 hours,=
 the
number of hours for which pay was guaranteed, his regular rate would be $22=
0.00
divided by 50 hours, or $4.40. He would be entitled to receive an additional
$22.00 for the 10 OT hours.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
