style=3D'line-height:115%'>In a week in which the employee worked 55 hours =
and
received under his contract or agreement the total amount of $250.00 ($220.=
00
under his guaranty and $20.00 as ST pay and $10.00 as OT premium for the fi=
ve
additional hours) his regular rate of pay would still be determined by divi=
ding
the amount of his guaranty, $220.00 by the number of hours for which pay was
guaranteed, 50 hours. His regular rate for that week would thus again be $4=
.40
and total compensation due would be ($220.00 + $22.00) + (5 X 1-1/2 X $4.40=
) or
$275.00. BW due would be $275.00 - $250.00 or $25.00.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
