e to
the work performed during OT hours.) If the circumstances are such that the
welders perform the janitorial work only in their OT hour., the $2 rate sha=
ll
be considered a bona fide rate for OT purposes provided it is the rate which
would have been paid to the welders had they performed the janitorial work =
in
nonovertime hours. The fact that the janitorial rate in this instance is 2/=
3 of
the welding rate (thus making the time and one-half OT rate for janitorial =
work
equal to the straight time rate for welding work) is not material so long as
the janitorial rate is a bona fide rate.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<h4><b>32h04&nbsp; Overtime compensation on other forms of pay.</b></h4>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in'><span style=3D'line-height=
