<h3>32i&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; OVERTIME BASED ON RATE ESTABLIS=
HED
AS OVERTIME RATE BY AGREEMENT OR UNDERSTANDING</h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<h4><b>32i00&nbsp;&nbsp; General provisions of FLSA Sec 7(g)(3).</b></h4>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in'><span style=3D'line-height=
:115%'>Sec
7(g)(3) permits the payment of OT compensation based on a rate not less than
one and one -half times the rate established by agreement or understanding
arrived at between the employer and the employee before performance of the
work, if the rate is authorized by Reg 548.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<h4><b>32i01&nbsp;&nbsp; Payments under Regulations, Part 548.</b></h4>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(a)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>Reg 548 provides for the exc=
lusion
of certain “additional” payments in cash or in kind which would have a triv=
ial
effect on OT compensation and which would otherwise require prorating over a
retroactive period to compute the OT due. Exclusions are limited to
“additional” or “incidental” payments; payments which are an “integral part=
” of
the employee’s regular wages may not be excluded.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(b)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>As a general rule, payments =
which
are regularly paid on every payday are not excludable as they are not
“additional”, but an integral part of the employee’s regular wages.
Furthermore, the mere fact that payments are deferred to a future time will=
 not
make them excludable as additional payments if they amount to nothing more =
than
an increase in the rate per hour or per piece. An exception is made for
payments in kind and certain cash payments, such as Social Security taxes w=
hich
are excludable even if paid every payday.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(c)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>An “additional” payment with=
in the
meaning of the Reg generally is one which is made on a different basis from
that which determines the wages to which the employee is regularly entitled=
 and
is not regularly made every payday.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(d)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>The following types of payme=
nt may
be excluded if the 50 cents condition and the requirements of 548.2 are met=
:</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(1)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp; </span></span><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>Prizes.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(2)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp; </span></span><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>Merchandise awards.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(3)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp; </span></span><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>Housing of nominal value.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(4)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp; </span></span><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>Lunches.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in'><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>(5)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>=
&nbsp; </span></span><span
style=3D'line-height:115%'>Social Security taxes.</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'line-height:115%'>&nbsp;</span></p>

